<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-256-904  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 256 904.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  March 19 1990 n459 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SI firms for sale in U.K. (systems integration)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Halper, Mark.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Several British systems integrators are looking for buyers whowill help the firms with large infusions of capital.andP;  The firmsare mainly looking abroad for potential buyers from the US, Japanand Western Europe.andP;  The firms rumored to be on the block include,Hoskyns Group plc, SD-Scicon plc, Sema Group plc and Logica plc.andO;The common thread among these companies is their need forincreased capital to allow them to compete in the unified Europeanmarket.andP;  Even the largest British firms are only mid-sized by USstandards, and in a market where it takes a lot of capital tocompete, these companies need big investors.andP;  This is the firsttime in the relatively young market that foreign companies areexpected to play a large role in the UK.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United KingdomComputer Systems IntegratorsCompaniesMarket ShareIndustry AnalysisFinancingAcquisition.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>